{
  "stem": "1581.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And to be honest, human nature is very strange.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember that these few months in 1944 when we knew that the war was lost for Germany-- there was absolutely no way how he could recover from all the events that had taken place.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now they were just fighting to stay alive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we knew we just had to hold on and maybe we will be able to survive it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then something happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This miserable, stinking, hungry, dysentery-plagued place overnight was built up to be a beautiful town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They started to make a park with a gazebo in it, and in this gazebo was a music band playing music in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People were strolling in the park, dressed much better.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were a street with a coffee house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was no coffee, but there was a coffee house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a bank.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no money, but there was a bank with the stores, and there were little playgrounds for children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was a soccer field.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, things that was unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we knew this is all phony and baloney because our life didn't [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Rations didn't become bigger.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we knew what it was all about because we were told there will be a movie crew to come in to film for the outside world.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "What a wonderful gift Hitler gave to the Jews, that he gave them a town which is more or less like a retirement place.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "By the way, the Germans that came with transports were under the-- were under the opinion that they came to a retirement place.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were told in Germany, they were given the order to pay I don't know how many thousands of marks because it is for their retirement in Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
